    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46), a hallmark of atmospheric performance. At its heart is the S54 3.2L inline-six, utilizing individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing for a high-revving, linear power delivery. This chassis has been proactively maintained, featuring rear subframe reinforcement and a refreshed VANOS unit to ensure long-term mechanical reliability. The 6-speed manual transmission delivers tactile shifts, paired with a variable M-differential lock for optimized torque distribution. Suspension has been upgraded with Bilstein dampers to sharpen turn-in response while maintaining high-speed stability. Though the exterior retains some minor road patina, the powertrain remains tight with excellent compression. This is a mechanically sorted example designed for the purist who values visceral feedback and engineering pedigree.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
